OL,3,CMajority of victims don't believe
OL,4,Creporting crimes leads to justice
OL,6,FShockingly, today's Victim
OL,7,FCommissioner's survey has revealed 73%
OL,8,Fof those surveyed were not confident
OL,9,Fthat reporting a crime would lead to
OL,10,Fjustice. Of those who did, 40% said
OL,11,Fthey were dissatisfied with the police
OL,12,Fresponse. And worryingly, despite
OL,13,Fbeing more likely to be victims of
OL,14,Fcrime, almost half (45%) of disabled
OL,15,Fvictims said they too were
OL,16,Fdissatisfied with the response and
OL,17,Fwere less likely to report a crime to
OL,18,Fthe police again.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
