OL,6,FThe Victims Commissioner, Baroness
OL,7,FHelen Newlove, told ITV News: "I think
OL,8,Fthey (victims) must feel dreadful...
OL,9,Fso disillusioned, disbelieved."
OL,11,F"If a person has been raped, sexually
OL,12,Fabused or been harmed... for somebody
OL,13,Fin authority that you think I can go
OL,14,Freport to, doesn't believe you. They
OL,15,Fwill feel internally that actually
OL,16,Fthey're guilty. It must be something
OL,17,Fwrong about them, and they'll have no
OL,18,Fconfidence within a system that should
OL,19,Fbe there to protect them, listen to
OL,20,Fthem and treat them with dignity."
